title: CBB final: Coleen Nolan and Jedward battle it out as Kim Woodburn leaves in third place
text:
Published 3rd February 2017 
The Loose Woman star defied all odds to be crowned winner of the 2017 series. 
The winning position slipped out of Jedward's hands as Emma Willis revealed they had been placed second. 

The crowd booed Kim as she left the compound tonight. 
She broke the internet when she joined the house three weeks ago, getting into explosive arguments with the other celebs. 
Her first big row was with Jamie O'Hara and she even got taken out of the house by security. 
EVICTED: Kim was greeted by boos 
She joined James Cosmo, Nicola McLean and Bianca Gascoigne. 
Bianca Gascoigne was the first to be evicted in the Celebrity Big Brother final tonight, coming in sixth place. 
She formed a steamy relationship with footballer Jamie O'Hara in the house who was waiting for her in the audience. 
Chanel 5 SIXTH PLACE: Bianca left the house first in the final   
Upon seeing each other outside the lovebirds waved to each other eagerly. 
Talking to Emma Willis Bianca said: "It's not been the same without him. I didn't believe he went. It was difficult I felt lonely in there. 
"I never expected to feel the way I do about Jamie." 
Just Coleen Nolan and Jedward remain in the house as they battle it out for first place.
